Hi,  I’m currently working on the translation into spanish (https://gist.github.com/Estebank97/e9a5246c264a69cc30b19ab7d0ac7e44) of the most complete documentation - with the exception of the whitepaper- I found, which is https://keep-network.gitbook.io/staking-documentation/keep-network-staking/keep-network-101.

Confusions while translating 
Maybe it’s just me, but I found some confusions which should be addressed in order to get people easily onboard IMHO.

#1) Many “keep” words involved
Keep …. the project
Keep Network … the network
KEEP … the token
Keep … the proper tECDSA Keep where private data chunk is hold
keep … the operator, the client, the node 

#2) operator, client, node
which one ? IMHO for simplicity we should just use one word.
Node is my favorite. Operator seems a human being. Client seems to be the client-side software or app. It is also primary used in the Whitepaper and on Github Repos.

#3) Dates
A lot of dates used in the document seem out of date and should be updated. @Matt Luongo @L i z
